          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ft8f52x/canvas/p3/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ft8f52x/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>If the fabric of historical Judaism is to be saved<lb/> from utter demolition, for,\n                on the score of Scriptural<lb/> Judaism, I have no fear, fair compromises must\n                be<lb/> made. I have long held out against changes by<lb/> individual congregations,\n                but our orthodox leaders<lb/> give no sign of life, utter no sound, to cheer\n                their<lb/> supporters and followers. The pressure from without<lb/> increases daily\n                in intensity, and the faithful <add>אבל</add><lb/> must either yield to the demands\n                made, or give<lb/> room to others who will effect a complete <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >bouleverse</hi><lb/><hi rend=\"underline\">ment</hi> of the existing state of\n                things.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have been interrupted for some hours by the<lb/> sad tidings of\n                the loss of the Evening Star. Some of the<lb/> passengers said to be lost have\n                relatives among my<lb/> congregation, but I declined to give <add>ר\"כ לנר</add>\n                until their<lb/> fate had been ascertained. I have however very little<lb/> hope of\n                their being alive.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Revenons à nos moutons. Have you read the articles<lb/> in the\n                “Archives Israelites” written by <persName>Cohen</persName>, Chief Rabbi<lb/> in\n                    <placeName>Algiers</placeName>, during the last few months? Their fairness\n                is<lb/> indisputable and their accuracy has not been impeached,<lb/> and, what is\n                more, cannot be. His account of the <add>ר\"כ לנר</add></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ft8f52x/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
