                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>or stream whose waters might have fructified Judaism.<lb/> I say it with pain, with\n                agony, that the want of such a Synod<lb/> has sent<add>?</add> Judaism to tatters,\n                that it has encouraged rationalism<lb/> in its destructive tendencies in the\n                    <placeName>west</placeName>, and promoted the<lb/> growth of that abominable\n                    stassidism<add>?</add> in the <placeName>east</placeName>. I have<lb/> some true\n                and good men among my people, who have <sic>travelled</sic><lb/> and seen much of\n                our various communities in <placeName>France</placeName>,<lb/>\n                <placeName>Germany</placeName>, <placeName>Austria</placeName>, and other parts of\n                    <placeName>Europe</placeName>. They are men<lb/> attached to the old system\n                still, with all its admitted defects,<lb/> and they lament with me the insouciance\n                with which the<lb/> orthodox Rabbis regard the spread of irreligion, particularly\n                the violation<lb/> of the <date>Sabbath</date>, and indulgence in forbidden food,\n                without a<lb/> united effort among them to check it by wise and well concocted<lb/>\n                measures. <add>ר\"ה</add>. There is, I sincerely believe, more taleah<lb/> and more\n                real learning among the orthodox than among the Reformers, and yet<lb/> they allow\n                this “laissez aller” <del>sent</del> state of things to go on. But<lb/> enough of\n                this for the present.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">And now for a little <add>שמחת תורה</add> relating to myself,\n                with<lb/> which I beg of you to occupy a trifle of your valuable time.<lb/> A\n                brother of mine recently informed me of his having met in\n                    <placeName>London</placeName><lb/>\n                <persName>Mr. Lem Dyer</persName>, brother of our lamented friend <persName>Mrs.\n                    Osterman</persName>,</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3ft8f52x/canvas/p6"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
