                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>who <del>info</del> mentioned to him that that lady had bequeathed me<lb/> and my\n                wife, a legacy of $3000 in her will. It is easy for<lb/> you, being in the spot, to\n                ascertain, either by writing to <persName>Mrs.<lb/> Symonds</persName>, formerly\n                    <persName>Hannah Dyer</persName>, at <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>, or\n                by<lb/> personal inquiry among her friends the <persName>Pollacks</persName>,\n                the<lb/> truth of my brother's statement. I have <sic>foreborne</sic> so long<lb/>\n                from addressing <persName>Mrs. S.</persName> not knowing her right address,<lb/>\n                that a direct inquiry from me now, would be indelicate.<lb/> I prefer you being my\n                agent in this to my brother's being so,<lb/> for various reasons. It will be\n                sufficient to quote the<lb/> words of <persName>Solomon</persName>\n                <add>ס\"ה</add>. You will be doing me<lb/> and your old friend <persName>Mrs.\n                    N</persName> a favor by losing no time<lb/> in letting us know\n                <add>קדיש</add>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Our Holy days passed off delightfully, full attendances<lb/> at\n                Synagogue, great devotion, order, and decorum, and nothing<lb/> to ruffle the\n                harmony from <add>תענו ותעתרו</add> on the eve<lb/> of that day I confirmed 5 young\n                people 3 girls and 2 boys.<lb/> Every child almost of 6 or 7 years of age, boy or\n                girl, learns<lb/> to read Hebrew, and nearly every lady in Synagogue,\n                particularly<lb/> the young and middle aged reads her prayers in that language,<lb/>\n                and can follow the leader officiating. Your small Bible</p>"
                  },
